%% Sequence Diagram — Benchmarking Harness Primary Flow (Happy Path + Tainted Iteration)
%% Import: Arrange → Insert → Mermaid → choose "Diagram"

sequenceDiagram
    title Benchmark Experiment — Primary Flow (Updated 2026-07-08)
    autonumber
    actor R as Researcher
    participant CLI as Orchestrator<br/>(Python CLI)
    participant HW as Hardware Probe<br/>(sysctl)
    participant PM as Prompt Manager<br/>(JSONL + SHA-256)
    participant TM as Thermal Monitor<br/>(powermetrics)
    participant ML as MLflow<br/>(local tracking)
    participant E as Engine<br/>(backend)
    participant MC as Metrics Computer<br/>(NumPy/SciPy)

    R->>+CLI: bench run config.yaml
    CLI->>+HW: capture system state
    HW-->>-CLI: M5 Max profile, OS, git SHA, lib versions
    CLI->>+PM: load dataset + verify SHA-256
    PM-->>-CLI: prompts[] (verified)
    CLI->>+TM: check baseline thermal
    TM-->>-CLI: OK (not throttling)
    CLI->>+ML: start_run(params)
    ML-->>-CLI: run_id

    Note over CLI,E: Correctness Gate (temp=0, fixed seed)
    CLI->>+E: generate(reference_prompt, temp=0, seed=42)
    E-->>-CLI: output
    CLI->>CLI: compare vs stored reference (bitwise)
    Note over CLI: PASS — proceed to warmup

    Note over CLI,E: Warmup Phase (N=10, discarded)
    loop 10 warmup iterations
        CLI->>E: generate(prompt, params)
        E-->>CLI: result (discarded)
    end

    Note over CLI,E: Measurement Phase (M=10, timed)
    loop 10 timed iterations
        CLI->>+TM: check thermal state
        TM-->>-CLI: thermal_reading
        CLI->>+E: generate(prompt, params)
        E-->>-CLI: GenerationResult{timestamps, memory, thermal}

        alt Thermal throttle detected mid-iteration
            TM-->>CLI: THROTTLE WARNING
            CLI->>CLI: flag iteration status=THERMAL_TAINTED
        end

        CLI->>CLI: wait cooldown (30s)
    end

    Note over CLI,MC: Metrics Computation
    CLI->>+MC: compute_stats(valid_iterations)
    MC-->>-CLI: p50/p90/p95/p99, mean, trimmed_mean, std, CoV

    alt CoV > 5%
        CLI->>CLI: flag run as unstable
    end

    CLI->>+ML: log_metrics + log_artifacts(parquet, plots)
    ML-->>-CLI: OK
    CLI-->>-R: Run complete. ID: {run_id}, Status: stable/unstable
